I think so,

It could be tune a bit better

```
std::pair<bool, nlohmann::json> getDimmInfo(const auto& pel)
{
   ...
   bool hasDIMMInfo = std::ranges::any_of(pel.optionalSections(), hasDimmInfo);
   return std::make_pair(hasDIMMInfo, hasDimmInfo);
}
```

This boolean could be used as an additional check within the EXPECT_X() for various test cases. Just a suggestion—I'm fine with the current implementation as well since your EXPECT_EQ will fail with an empty JSON object.

@Matt , Yes since some PELs have multiple user data section and our intention find the UD with DIMM info . Hence stopping the further search once it finds the match.

@Ramesh, It seems some typo here , return std::make_pair(hasDIMMInfo, hasDimmInfo); Did you meant 'dimmInfo' instead of 'hasDimmInfo'?
As per the current logic , I feel return value of any_of is less important as I am comparing the fetched JSON object from the UD section with the expected json object.
